The `Window*`in the error is actually the data type of the first member of struct being stored in the union. e.g. take this code

```
struct point {
    short x, y;
};
struct obj {
    char val;
    union {
        struct point p;
        void *r;
    } data;
};

int main()
{
    // This builds
    struct obj test1 = {.val = 0, .data.p = {.x=2,.y=3}};

    struct point p = {.x = 1, .y = 0};

    // This will fail
    struct obj test2 = {.val = 0, .data.p = p};
    return 0;
}
```

The error will be 

```
test.c(20) : error C2440: 'initializing' : cannot convert from 'point' to 'short'
```

But if you change the data type for `x` in `struct point` into something else, then you will get that data type instead of short.

